Purpose of this programming code

This is the (now slightly improved) code I used for my publication âPolygraphia III: The cipher that pretends to be an artificial languageâ, which I presented at the International Voynich Conference 2022 and which is published here: https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-3313/

Examined Texts

Specifically, various characteristics of different texts are examined: - The text of the Voynich Manuscript - Early modern texts in different languages - Texts encoded with the Polygraphia III method

Examined Features

The features under investigation are: - The word length distribution of types and tokens - Different entropy values - The number of adjacency word repetitions and minimal pairs.
